<item>
            <title>[SLING-1326] LogConfigManager: Access to internal configuration maps is not thread-safe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SLING-1326</link>
                <project id="12310710" key="SLING">Sling</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The LogConfigManager class has a number of maps to internally manage configurations and writers and logger categories. Access to these maps is not thread-safe and might lead to endless loops if maps get corrupted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To fix issue, it would probably be easiest to replace the HashMap obejdcts by ConcurrentHashMap objects.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
